# Epoch Buddy Project Context

## Product Surfaces

- This package includes four user-facing surfaces: the extension menu/popup, the extension content script, the demo website, and the listing/marketing pages.
- Treat changes as part of one product: keep terminology, timestamp behavior, privacy claims, and offline-first messaging aligned across those surfaces.
- Preserve the product promise: fast epoch/date conversion, no external network dependency, and no telemetry by default.

## Nomenclature

- Popup: The extension menu/popup which contains the conversion tabs and history.
- Content Script: The extension content-script which adds popup to the page on selection.
- Demo: The demo website hosted on GitHub Pages.
- Listing: The listing/marketing pages for the extension in the Chrome Web Store and Firefox Add-ons.

## Source Of Truth

- `src/popup/main.js` is the source for the extension menu logic.
- `src/content/main.js` is the source for the extension content-script logic.
- `src/demo/main.js` is the source for the demo website logic.
- `src/shared/*.js` contains shared behavior used across surfaces.
- `docs/index.html`, `docs/privacy.html`, `docs/terms.html`, `docs/styles.css`, and `docs/nav.js` are hand-authored listing/site files.

## Build outputs (do not hand-edit)

- **esbuild** bundles `src/**` entry points to `extension/index.js`, `extension/script.js`, `docs/demo.js`, and `docs/nav.js`.
- Do not manually edit those generated files unless the task is explicitly about build artifacts; change `src/**`, or `scripts/build.mjs`, then run `npm run build`.

## Working Preference

- When the request touches extension behavior, decide whether it belongs to popup code, content-script code, demo code, or listing-page content before editing.
- Reuse shared helpers instead of duplicating timestamp parsing, formatting, clipboard, or theme logic across surfaces.
